      Published Feb 11, 2015 by drew p.












13,214 of 13,590 people found the following review helpful
Drew Peretzky
If you're reading this review you've probably been in the mattress market for a while. 

I spent hours online researching mattresses and came to realize what a racket this can be. It's impossible to compare products and all of them seem to have unhappy customers that have to jump through hoops to get any warranty satisfaction. I suddenly noticed how many mattress stores there are! Not something that you notice until you're looking for one. Obviously there is a huge mark-up on a mattress or there wouldn't be so many vendors in the marketplace. We actually went to a store - the "Numbers" mattress store, where you essentially inflate a bag to get the firmness you want - for big dollars. Fortunately my wife and I are the same "number" so we didn't really need the individual adjustability, but we would never have gone for it anyway - the quality just wasn't there and the price was silly - even if you didn't add the hundreds of dollars worth of pillows, and accessory "options".

Somehow I stumbled on the Saatva site and read with some astonishment the endless 5 star reviews. When I looked at the construction I was impressed with the quality features - no gimmicks. The warranty is superior to any others and they actually honor it. I could never imagine ordering such an important purchase over the internet - but I figured with the return policy I really couldn't lose.

We received our luxury firm mattress in early December and it has been wonderful. I actually look forward to falling into bed every night. The mattress itself was beautifully made of high quality materials, The delivery process was totally smooth and professional. Two months later we couldn't be happier with the quality and comfort, and the price is a bargain in my opinion.

I have only the highest praise for the product, the service, and the value for money. 

BTW this review is completely voluntary - I have not been solicited, paid or in any way induced by Saatva. 

We all need to support and encourage the growth of USA made products -especially when they are of exemplary quality.Was this review helpful to you? Yes No 







