Thank you Saatva!
I received your mattess almost 2 weeks ago. I had been "nervous" about ordering a mattress from an online store, but I did alot of research before finally choosing a Satvaa mattress. I was replacing a mattress from a well-known company. It was a torture chamber from day 1 as I felt like I was sleeping on the side of a mountain about to fall in to an abyss. Within 2 years a piece of the frame (plastic) broke and I had to take the whole thing apart to fix the frame. I was still sleeping on the side of a mountain....then the sides started to bulge out and the mattress would slide all over the base and the base would slide all over the floor. There was no helpful customer support, the mattress and base were made of shoddy materials, the whole thing started to fall apart within 5 years and was wildly overpriced. One of the air chambers finally popped and I was glad it did so I could get a traditional mattress and box spring, The day my Saatva mattress was to be delivered I took apart the old mattress and frame to toss it, and when I unzipped the cover and lifted up the foam beneath it I found black mold under the foam and top of the air chambers. I would have been delighted to sleep in a doggie bed at that point. Then the saatva arrived right on time and was delivered by polite and nice delivery men. When they left, I couldn't wait to put on sheets and try it out!  I could not believe how comfortable the bed was! For the first time in years I could sleep on my stomach and sides without pain, numbness and tingling! I forgot to mention that I am loaded with atthritis and within the last 9 years have had to have 2 back surgeries, 2 knee replacements and a right hip replacement. Bottom line...I sleep like a baby on this mattress and I am so happy I decided to take a "leap of faith" and trust the company and their incredible customer service and return policy. Thanks Saatva!Was this review helpful to you? Yes No 







