Tempur-Pedic International, Inc. is a manufacturer and distributor of mattress and pillows sold in more than 80 countries globally. Tempur-Pedic also has a health care channel which sells to hospitals, long-term care facilities, medical practices, and health care retailers. The company… MoreTempur-Pedic International, Inc. is a manufacturer and distributor of mattress and pillows sold in more than 80 countries globally. Tempur-Pedic also has a health care channel which sells to hospitals, long-term care facilities, medical practices, and health care retailers. The company has three main locations : The R&D center is located in Duffield, VA. This location conducts technology, product testing, and product development. Another R&D center is located in Aarup, Denmark, and conducts technology and product development. The final location is in Albuquerque, NM.
Tempur-Pedic International, Inc. is a manufacturer and distributor of mattress and pillows sold in more than 80 countries globally. Tempur-Pedic also has a health care channel which sells to hospitals, long-term care facilities, medical practices, and health care retailers. The company… MoreTempur-Pedic International, Inc. is a manufacturer and distributor of mattress and pillows sold in more than 80 countries globally. Tempur-Pedic also has a health care channel which sells to hospitals, long-term care facilities, medical practices, and health care retailers. The company has three main locations : The R&D center is located in Duffield, VA. This location conducts technology, product testing, and product development. Another R&D center is located in Aarup, Denmark, and conducts technology and product development. The final location is in Albuquerque, NM.

 IT Priorities
•Tempur Sealy is currently working to consolidate the company's systems in Microsoft Dynamics from other ERP platforms.

IT Structure •The primary focus of the IT department at Tempur Sealy International is to support the company's manufacturing, distribution, supply-chain, and mattress design.
•The company uses Oracle applications for its ERP system, including the databases, accounting and financial systems. However, the company is currently transitioning away from Oracle to Microsoft Dynamics for its ERP solutions.

The IT budget is typically finalized in Q4.

IT Intelligence Snippets
2012:
•Tempur-Pedic and Sealy Corporation recently merged to form Tempur Sealy International.
•Migrated its email to Microsoft Office from Lotus Notes
•Implemented new VoIP solution in its North Carolina office.

2012:
•Expecting IT storage spending to increase in the areas of data protection and recovery software, storage replication software, archiving software storage related cloud initiatives, and BigData initiatives. 
•Tempur Sealy International, Inc. describes Oracle as its biggest storage headache. Its top storage pain points are WAN being too slow, WAN optimization being too expensive, and the lack of modernizing/virtualizing solutions for systems and tape that are no longer viable. 
•Tempur Sealy International, Inc. uses disk backup across SANDAS environment to back up its block data. 
•It uses Veritas NetBackup with one master and media server as its main backup application. Its daily and weekly total data backup is 4TBTB and 8TB respectively, with a 5-6 hour backup window. Its backup growth is around 500GB. 
•Relating to its remote locations, data is backed up locally, and all remote locations have WAN optimization deployed.





