Tempur Sealy International, Inc. (NYSE: TPX) is an American manufacturer of mattresses and bedding products. It was formed when Tempur-Pedic International, a manufacturer of memory foam mattresses acquired its biggest competitor Sealy Corporation in 2012. It is based in Lexington, Kentucky.
